(41, 3, 14, 48, 1, 1, 1, 'that he might send them forth to preach', 'Apostolic Authority and Mission', 'This connection highlights the theme of apostolic authority, as both passages discuss the sending of individuals for a divine purpose. Mark 3:14 emphasizes Jesus ordaining the twelve to preach, while Galatians 1:1 presents Paul as an apostle sent by Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 3, 14, 48, 1, 15, 20, 'that they should be with him, and that he might send them forth to preach', 'Apostolic Calling and Preaching', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being called to preach. In Mark, the twelve are ordained to preach, while in Galatians, Paul speaks of being called to preach among the heathen.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
